  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'Perfect! The prompt has been generated successfully. Now I need to use the \'content\' field from the return result as my final output.\n\nYou are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: cryptography.\n\n--- 【EXPERT KNOWLEDGE & STRATEGIC GUIDANCE】 ---\nBased on the build log analysis:\n\n**Build Error Analysis:**\nThe Docker build succeeded but the fuzzer compilation failed with OpenSSL version error. The key error is:\n```\ncargo:warning=/src/cryptography/target/release/build/cryptography-cffi-e69366a768404201/out/_openssl.c:624:10: error: "pyca/cryptography MUST be linked with OpenSSL 3.0.0 or later"\n```\n\n**Root Cause:**\nThe cryptography package requires OpenSSL 3.0.0 or later, but the system has OpenSSL 1.1.1f. The log shows:\n```\nlibssl-dev is already the newest version (1.1.1f-1ubuntu2.24).\n```\n\n**Current State Analysis:**\n1. **Docker Build**: Successfully built with `base-builder-python` image\n2. **Dockerfile Issues**: Fixed the image reference format (now using `base-builder-python@sha256:...`)\n3. **Missing Component**: The previous fix removed OpenSSL 3.0.9 source build, assuming base image includes it\n4. **Actual Problem**: Base image includes OpenSSL 1.1.1, but cryptography requires 3.0.0+\n\n**Pattern Recognition:**\nThis is a common issue with cryptography projects that have strict OpenSSL version requirements. The package has compile-time checks that enforce OpenSSL 3.0.0+.\n\n**Fix Strategy:**\n1. **Restore OpenSSL 3.0+ Installation**: Need to install OpenSSL 3.0.0 or later\n2. **Options**:\n   a. Re-add the OpenSSL 3.0.9 source build that was previously in the Dockerfile\n   b. Use Ubuntu backports or PPA to install OpenSSL 3.0+\n   c. Build from source with proper configuration\n3. **Environment Variables**: Ensure LD_LIBRARY_PATH and PKG_CONFIG_PATH point to the correct OpenSSL 3.0+ installation\n\n**Specific Issues in Current Configuration:**\n1. The Dockerfile removed OpenSSL source build\n2. Environment variables point to `/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu` which contains OpenSSL 1.1.1\n3. Need to point to OpenSSL 3.0+ installation location\n\n**Additional Context:**\nThe original Dockerfile had OpenSSL 3.0.9 source build that installed to `/usr/local/ssl`. This should be restored or an equivalent OpenSSL 3.0+ installation method should be implemented.\n\n**Critical Path:**\n1. Install OpenSSL 3.0.9 (or later) from source\n2. Update environment variables to point to `/usr/local/ssl/lib64`\n3. Ensure build.sh uses the correct paths\n4. Verify that cryptography can find and link against OpenSSL 3.0+\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] Docker build failed due to invalid image reference format. The patch tool incorrectly modified the FROM line by placing the \'-python\' suffix after the SHA256 digest instead of before it. The correct format should be \'gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-python@sha256:...\' or \'gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:...\'. This is a configuration syntax error that needs to be fixed in the Dockerfile.\n- [Attempt 3] Docker build continues to fail with invalid image reference format. The core issue remains: the Dockerfile has malformed image name \'base-builder@sha256:...-python\' where \'-python\' suffix is incorrectly placed after the digest. Previous attempts show this is a recurring issue. Need to fundamentally fix the Dockerfile patching logic or manually correct the image reference to proper format: either \'base-builder-python@sha256:...\' or use a tagged version instead of digest.\n- [Attempt 4] Build progressed from Dockerfile syntax error to OpenSSL version mismatch error. The cryptography package requires OpenSSL 3.0.0+, but the base-builder-python image includes OpenSSL 1.1.1. The previous fix incorrectly removed the OpenSSL 3.0.9 source build that was needed. Need to restore OpenSSL 3.0+ installation, either by re-adding the source build or finding alternative installation method. This is a dependency version issue rather than configuration syntax error.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-python@sha256:76fc4d8513691cfd7031464348a8fe46810c243c04344fe6211363bcdd6d245e\n\nRUN git clone https://github.com/pyca/cryptography\nRUN apt-get update\nRUN apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev libffi-dev pkg-config python3-dev cargo -y\n# Install OpenSSL 3.0 or later from backports or build from source\n# Note: base-builder-python already includes OpenSSL, so we don\'t need to build it from source\n# Remove OpenSSL source build to avoid conflicts with pre-installed OpenSSL\nENV LD_LIBRARY_PATH="/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}"\nENV PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/pkgconfig:${PKG_CONFIG_PATH}"\nRUN pip3 install --upgrade pip\nRUN curl https://sh.rustup.rs -sSf | sh -s -- -y\n\nENV PATH="/root/.cargo/bin:${PATH}"\nRUN rustup install nightly\nRUN rustup default nightly\nWORKDIR cryptography\n\nCOPY build.sh fuzz_*.py $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n# Build fuzzers in $OUT.\npython3 -m pip cache purge\n# Compiling with sancov is causing some issues at the moment. This is likely\n# due to some missing flags propagated throughout.\nunset RUSTFLAGS\nunset CXXFLAGS\nunset CFLAGS\n# Set OpenSSL environment variables for building\nexport LD_LIBRARY_PATH="/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}"\nexport PKG_CONFIG_PATH="/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/pkgconfig:${PKG_CONFIG_PATH}"\npython3 -m pip install .\n\ncd $SRC\nfor fuzzer in $(find $SRC -name \'fuzz_*.py\'); do\n   compile_python_fuzzer $fuzzer \ndone\n\n### Content from: fuzz_aead.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/python3\n\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\nimport sys\nimport atheris\nwith atheris.instrument_imports():\n    import cryptography.hazmat.primitives.ciphers.aead as aead\n\ndef TestInput(input_bytes):\n    if len(input_bytes) < 12:\n        return\n\n    fdp = atheris.FuzzedDataProvider(input_bytes)\n\n    choice = fdp.ConsumeIntInRange(1,4)\n\n    if choice == 1:\n        cipher = aead.ChaCha20Poly1305(aead.ChaCha20Poly1305.generate_key())\n    if choice == 2:\n        cipher = aead.AESGCM(aead.AESGCM.generate_key(bit_length=128))\n    if choice == 3:\n        cipher = aead.AESOCB3(aead.AESOCB3.generate_key(bit_length=128))\n    if choice == 4:\n        cipher = aead.AESCCM(aead.AESCCM.generate_key(bit_length=128))\n   \n    msg = fdp.ConsumeBytes(32)\n    authentext =  fdp.ConsumeBytes(32)\n    nonce = fdp.ConsumeBytes(12)\n   \n    if len(nonce) < 12:\n        return\n\n    ciphertext = cipher.encrypt(nonce, msg, authentext)\n    plaintext = cipher.decrypt(nonce, ciphertext, authentext)\n\n    assert (plaintext == msg), "Encryption/Decrption error!"\n\ndef main():\n    atheris.Setup(sys.argv, TestInput, enable_python_coverage=False)\n    atheris.instrument_all()\n    atheris.Fuzz()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n   main()\n\n### Content from: fuzz_dh.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/python3\n\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\nimport sys\nimport atheris\nwith atheris.instrument_imports():\n    from cryptography.hazmat.primitives import hashes\n    from cryptography.hazmat.primitives.asymmetric import dh\n    from cryptography.hazmat.primitives.kdf.hkdf import HKDF\n\ndef TestInput(input_bytes):\n    fdp = atheris.FuzzedDataProvider(input_bytes)\n\n    try:\n        parameters = dh.generate_parameters(\n            generator=(2 if fdp.ConsumeBool() else 5), \n            key_size=fdp.ConsumeInt(4)\n        )\n    except ValueError as e:\n        # This can only happen if the key_size isn\'t valid\n        return\n\n    server_private_key = parameters.generate_private_key()\n    peer_private_key = parameters.generate_private_key()\n    server_derived_shared_key = server_private_key.exchange(peer_private_key.public_key())\n    peer_derived_shared_key = peer_private_key.exchange(server_private_key.public_key())\n\n    infobytes = fdp.ConsumeBytes(10)\n\n    server_derived_key = HKDF(\n        algorithm=hashes.SHA256(),\n        length=32,\n        salt=None,\n        info=infobytes,\n    ).derive(server_derived_shared_key)\n\n    peer_derived_key = HKDF(\n        algorithm=hashes.SHA256(),\n        length=32,\n        salt=None,\n        info=infobytes,\n    ).derive(peer_derived_shared_key)\n\n    assert (server_derived_key == peer_derived_key), "Key Derivation Error!!"\n\ndef main():\n    atheris.Setup(sys.argv, TestInput, enable_python_coverage=False)\n    atheris.instrument_all()\n    atheris.Fuzz()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    main()\n\n### Content from: fuzz_dsa.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/python3\n\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\nimport sys\nimport atheris\nwith atheris.instrument_imports():\n    from cryptography.hazmat.primitives import hashes\n    from cryptography.hazmat.primitives.asymmetric import dsa, utils\n\ndef TestInput(input_bytes):\n    fdp = atheris.FuzzedDataProvider(input_bytes)\n\n    private_key = dsa.generate_private_key(key_size=1024)\n    public_key = private_key.public_key()\n\n    data = fdp.ConsumeBytes(20)\n    more_data = fdp.ConsumeBytes(20)\n\n    hasher = hashes.Hash(hashes.SHA256())\n    hasher.update(data)\n    hasher.update(more_data)\n    digest = hasher.finalize()\n\n    sig1 = private_key.sign(data,hashes.SHA256())\n    sig2 = private_key.sign(digest,utils.Prehashed(hashes.SHA256()))\n\n    public_key.verify(sig1,data,hashes.SHA256())\n    public_key.verify(sig2,digest,utils.Prehashed(hashes.SHA256()))\n\ndef main():\n    atheris.Setup(sys.argv, TestInput, enable_python_coverage=False)\n    atheris.instrument_all()\n    atheris.Fuzz()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    main()\n\n### Content from: fuzz_sym.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/python3\n\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\nimport sys\nimport base64\nimport atheris\nwith atheris.instrument_imports():\n     from cryptography.fernet import Fernet\n     from cryptography.hazmat.primitives import hashes\n     from cryptography.hazmat.primitives.kdf.pbkdf2 import PBKDF2HMAC\n\ndef TestInput(input_bytes):\n    fdp = atheris.FuzzedDataProvider(input_bytes)\n    plaintext = fdp.ConsumeBytes(32)\n\n    key = Fernet(Fernet.generate_key())\n    token = key.encrypt(plaintext)\n    text = key.decrypt(token)\n    assert (plaintext == text), "Encryption/Decrption error!"\n\n    password = fdp.ConsumeBytes(8)\n    salt = fdp.ConsumeBytes(16)\n    kdf = PBKDF2HMAC(\n        algorithm=hashes.SHA256(),\n        length=32,\n        salt=salt,\n        iterations=1,\n    )\n    key = Fernet(base64.urlsafe_b64encode(kdf.derive(password)))\n    token = key.encrypt(plaintext)\n    text = key.decrypt(token)\n    assert (plaintext == text), "Encryption/Decrption error!"\n\ndef main():\n    atheris.Setup(sys.argv, TestInput, enable_python_coverage=False)\n    atheris.Fuzz()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    main()\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nauto_ccs:\n- paul.l.kehrer@gmail.com\nfuzzing_engines:\n- libfuzzer\nhomepage: https://github.com/pyca/cryptography\nlanguage: python\nmain_repo: https://github.com/pyca/cryptography\nprimary_contact: alex.gaynor@gmail.com\nsanitizers:\n- address\nvendor_ccs:\n- david@adalogics.com\n- adam@adalogics.com\n- arthur.chan@adalogics.com\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 cryptography\n├── 📄 CHANGELOG.rst\n├── 📄 CONTRIBUTING.rst\n├── 📄 Cargo.lock\n├── 📄 Cargo.toml\n├── 📄 LICENSE\n├── 📄 LICENSE.APACHE\n├── 📄 LICENSE.BSD\n├── 📄 README.rst\n├── 📄 ci-constraints-requirements.txt\n├── 📁 docs\n├── 📄 noxfile.py\n├── 📄 pyproject.toml\n├── 📄 release.py\n├── 📁 src\n├── 📁 tests\n└── 📁 vectors\n\n--- Recent Commit Changes ---\nNo relevant commit found.\n\n--- Fuzz Build Log (Last 500 lines) ---\n(Reading database ... 60%\n(Reading database ... 65%\n(Reading database ... 70%\n(Reading database ... 75%\n(Reading database ... 80%\n(Reading database ... 85%\n(Reading database ... 90%\n(Reading database ... 95%\n(Reading database ... 100%\n(Reading database ... 17483 files and directories currently installed.)\n#8 13.62 Preparing to unpack .../libpython3.8-minimal_3.8.10-0ubuntu1~20.04.18_'}
